@startuml activity-unified-history
'' PlantUML over Mermaid: this view emphasises that MANY input affordances converge on ONE history
'' mechanism (a fan-in to nav/step + nav-active) with a kind-of-navigation branch — an activity diagram
'' with swimlane ownership + a decision expresses that better than a flowchart. Colours: blue-violet
'' APPDB = app-db per-tab history; teal RENDERER = re-frame events.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Unified history spine — every navigation affordance is one interface over one mechanism

|#7590DB|Affordance (input)|
start
:Any navigation affordance —
toolbar Back/Forward, **Alt+Left / Alt+Right** (all keymaps),
mouse thumb buttons, web-view back/forward (vv:history-nav),
**Alt+Up** / **Alt+Down**, breadcrumb-segment click,
file / link / tree click, URI bar Enter, File ▸ Open Recent;

|#2D9574|Renderer (re-frame events)|
:resolver / command registry / UI dispatches a navigation event;
if (kind of navigation?) then (back / forward)
  :[:history/back] / [:history/forward];
  |#7590DB|app-db history (vinary.app.nav)|
  :**nav/step ±1**\nmove [:hist :idx]; restore that entry's scroll;
else (open / push)
  |#2D9574|Renderer (re-frame events)|
  :[:tab/navigate] / [:doc/open] /\n[:nav/parent] / [:nav/open-target];
  note right
    A directory opens the same way as a file
    (:tab/navigate / :doc/open), so **filesystem
    navigation is part of history** — Alt+Left
    undoes an Alt+Up.
  end note
  |#7590DB|app-db history (vinary.app.nav)|
  :**nav/nav-active**\npush {:uri :scroll}; truncate forward entries;
endif

:active tab :uri := current history entry;
:retained-file-paths → main watcher / DataScript cache ownership;
:load local content [:vv/open] + [:scroll/restore];
stop

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  |<#7590DB>| app-db — per-tab history (vinary.app.nav) |
  |<#2D9574>| Renderer — re-frame events |
endlegend
@enduml
